7992static gboolean parse_PA_Attribute(proto_tree *parentTree, tvbuff_t *tvb, gint *offset, MAD_t *MAD, RMPP_t *RMPP, PA_HEADER_t *PA_HEADER)
7993{
7994 gint local_offset = *offset;
7995
7996 switch (MAD->AttributeID) {
7997 case PA_ATTR_ID_CLASS_PORTINFO0x0001:
7998 local_offset = parse_ClassPortInfo(parentTree, tvb, &local_offset, MAD);
7999 break;
8000 case PA_ATTR_ID_GET_GRP_LIST0x00A0:
8001 local_offset = parse_GetGroupList(parentTree, tvb, &local_offset, MAD, RMPP, PA_HEADER);
8002 break;
8003 case PA_ATTR_ID_GET_GRP_INFO0x00A1:
8004 local_offset = parse_GetGroupInfo(parentTree, tvb, &local_offset, MAD, RMPP, PA_HEADER);
8005 break;
8006 case PA_ATTR_ID_GET_GRP_CFG0x00A2:
8007 local_offset = parse_GetGroupConfig(parentTree, tvb, &local_offset, MAD, RMPP, PA_HEADER);
8008 break;
8009 case PA_ATTR_ID_GET_PORT_CTRS0x00A3:
8010 local_offset = parse_GetPortCounters(parentTree, tvb, &local_offset, MAD);
8011 break;
8012 case PA_ATTR_ID_CLR_PORT_CTRS0x00A4:
8013 local_offset = parse_ClearPortCounters(parentTree, tvb, &local_offset);
8014 break;
8015 case PA_ATTR_ID_CLR_ALL_PORT_CTRS0x00A5:
8016 local_offset = parse_ClearAllPortCounters(parentTree, tvb, &local_offset);
8017 break;
8018 case PA_ATTR_ID_GET_PM_CFG0x00A6:
8019 local_offset = parse_PMConfig(parentTree, tvb, &local_offset);
8020 break;
8021 case PA_ATTR_ID_FREEZE_IMAGE0x00A7:
8022 local_offset = parse_Image(parentTree, tvb, &local_offset);
8023 break;
8024 case PA_ATTR_ID_RELEASE_IMAGE0x00A8:
8025 local_offset = parse_Image(parentTree, tvb, &local_offset);
8026 break;
8027 case PA_ATTR_ID_RENEW_IMAGE0x00A9:
8028 local_offset = parse_Image(parentTree, tvb, &local_offset);
8029 break;
8030 case PA_ATTR_ID_GET_FOCUS_PORTS0x00AA:
8031 local_offset = parse_GetFocusPorts(parentTree, tvb, &local_offset, MAD, RMPP, PA_HEADER);
8032 break;
8033 case PA_ATTR_ID_GET_IMAGE_INFO0x00AB:
8034 local_offset = parse_GetImageInfo(parentTree, tvb, &local_offset);
8035 break;
8036 case PA_ATTR_ID_MOVE_FREEZE_FRAME0x00AC:
8037 local_offset = parse_MoveFreezeFrame(parentTree, tvb, &local_offset);
8038 break;
8039 case PA_ATTR_ID_GET_VF_LIST0x00AD:
8040 local_offset = parse_GetVFList(parentTree, tvb, &local_offset, MAD, RMPP, PA_HEADER);
8041 break;
8042 case PA_ATTR_ID_GET_VF_INFO0x00AE:
8043 local_offset = parse_GetVFInfo(parentTree, tvb, &local_offset, MAD, RMPP, PA_HEADER);
8044 break;
8045 case PA_ATTR_ID_GET_VF_CONFIG0x00AF:
8046 local_offset = parse_GetVFConfig(parentTree, tvb, &local_offset, MAD, RMPP, PA_HEADER);
8047 break;
8048 case PA_ATTR_ID_GET_VF_PORT_CTRS0x00B0:
8049 local_offset = parse_GetVFPortCounters(parentTree, tvb, &local_offset, MAD);
8050 break;
8051 case PA_ATTR_ID_CLR_VF_PORT_CTRS0x00B1:
8052 local_offset = parse_ClearVFPortCounters(parentTree, tvb, &local_offset);
8053 break;
8054 case PA_ATTR_ID_GET_VF_FOCUS_PORTS0x00B2:
8055 local_offset = parse_GetVFFocusPorts(parentTree, tvb, &local_offset, MAD, RMPP, PA_HEADER);
8056 break;
8057 default:
8058 return FALSE(0);
8059 }
8060
8061 *offset = local_offset;
8062 return TRUE(!(0));
8063}
8064
8065/* Parse the Method from the MAD Common Header. */
8066static void label_PA_Method(proto_item *PAItem, MAD_t *MAD, packet_info *pinfo)
8067{
8068 const guchar *label = val_to_str_const(MAD->Method, PA_Methods, "(Unknown Perf Method!)");
8069 proto_item_append_text(PAItem, " %s", label);
8070 col_append_str(pinfo->cinfo, COL_INFO, label);
8071}
8072
8073/* Parse the Attribute from the MAD Common Header */
8074static void label_PA_Attribute(proto_item *PAItem, MAD_t *MAD, packet_info *pinfo)
8075{
8076 const guchar *label = val_to_str_const(MAD->AttributeID, PA_Attributes, "Attribute (Unknown Perf Attribute!)");
8077 proto_item_append_text(PAItem, "%s", &label[11]);
8078 col_append_str(pinfo->cinfo, COL_INFO, &label[11]);
8079}
8080/* Parse the PA_HEADER
8081* IN: parentTree to add the dissection to
8082* IN: tvb - the data buffer from wireshark
8083* IN/OUT: The current and updated offset */
8084static gboolean parse_PA_HEADER(proto_tree *parentTree, packet_info *pinfo, tvbuff_t *tvb, gint *offset, MAD_t *MAD, PA_HEADER_t *PA_HEADER)
8085{
8086 gint local_offset = *offset;
8087 proto_item *PA_HEADER_header_item;
8088 proto_tree *PA_HEADER_header_tree;
8089
8090 PA_HEADER_header_item = proto_tree_add_item(parentTree, hf_opa_pa, tvb, local_offset, 20, ENC_NA0x00000000);
8091 PA_HEADER_header_tree = proto_item_add_subtree(PA_HEADER_header_item, ett_pa);
8092
8093 PA_HEADER->SM_Key = tvb_get_ntoh64(tvb, local_offset);
8094 proto_tree_add_item(PA_HEADER_header_tree, hf_opa_pa_sm_key, tvb, local_offset, 8, ENC_BIG_ENDIAN0x00000000);
8095 local_offset += 8;
8096 PA_HEADER->AttributeOffset = tvb_get_ntohs(tvb, local_offset);
8097 proto_tree_add_item(PA_HEADER_header_tree, hf_opa_pa_attribute_offset, tvb, local_offset, 2, ENC_BIG_ENDIAN0x00000000);
8098 local_offset += 2;
8099 PA_HEADER->Reserved = tvb_get_ntohs(tvb, local_offset);
8100 proto_tree_add_item(PA_HEADER_header_tree, hf_opa_reserved16, tvb, local_offset, 2, ENC_BIG_ENDIAN0x00000000);
8101 local_offset += 2;
8102 PA_HEADER->ComponentMask = tvb_get_ntoh64(tvb, local_offset);
8103 proto_tree_add_item(PA_HEADER_header_tree, hf_opa_pa_component_mask, tvb, local_offset, 8, ENC_BIG_ENDIAN0x00000000);
8104 local_offset += 8;
8105
8106 label_PA_Method(PA_HEADER_header_item, MAD, pinfo);
8107 label_PA_Attribute(PA_HEADER_header_item, MAD, pinfo);
8108
8109 *offset = local_offset;
8110 return TRUE(!(0));
8111}
8112/* Parse Performance Administration */
8113static void parse_PERFADMN(proto_tree *parentTree, packet_info *pinfo, tvbuff_t *tvb, gint *offset)
8114{
8115 MAD_t MAD;
8116 RMPP_t RMPP;
8117 PA_HEADER_t PA_HEADER;
8118
8119 if (!parse_MAD_Common(parentTree, pinfo, tvb, offset, &MAD)) {
8120 return;
8121 }
8122 if (!parse_RMPP(parentTree, pinfo, tvb, offset, &RMPP)) {
8123 return;
8124 }
8125 if (!parse_PA_HEADER(parentTree, pinfo, tvb, offset, &MAD, &PA_HEADER)) {
8126 return;
8127 }
8128 if ((!pref_parse_on_mad_status_error && MAD.Status) ||
8129 RMPP.Type == RMPP_ACK2 ||
8130 (RMPP.Type == RMPP_DATA1 && RMPP.SegmentNumber != 1)) {
8131 *offset += tvb_captured_length_remaining(tvb, *offset);
8132 return;
8133 }
8134
8135 if (!parse_PA_Attribute(parentTree, tvb, offset, &MAD, &RMPP, &PA_HEADER)) {
8136 expert_add_info_format(pinfo, NULL((void*)0), &ei_opa_mad_no_attribute_dissector,
8137 "Attribute Dissector Not Implemented (0x%x)", MAD.AttributeID);
8138 *offset += tvb_captured_length_remaining(tvb, *offset);
8139 return;
8140 }
8141}
8142/* Parse Vendor Specific Management Packets */
8143/* TBD: Replace with dissector table to call other possible dissectors */
8144static void parse_VENDOR_MANAGEMENT(proto_tree *parentTree, packet_info *pinfo, tvbuff_t *tvb, gint *offset)
8145{
8146 MAD_t MAD;
8147 RMPP_t RMPP;
8148
8149 if (!parse_MAD_Common(parentTree, pinfo, tvb, offset, &MAD)) {
8150 return;
8151 }
8152 if (value_is_in_range(global_mad_vendor_class, MAD.MgmtClass)) {
8153 /* Vendor MAD 0x09 to 0x0F does NOT have an RMPP header */
8154
8155 } else if (value_is_in_range(global_mad_vendor_rmpp_class, MAD.MgmtClass)) {
8156 /* Vendor MAD 0x30 to 0x4F has an RMPP header */
8157 if (!parse_RMPP(parentTree, pinfo, tvb, offset, &RMPP)) {
8158 return;
8159 }
8160 }
8161 if (!pref_parse_on_mad_status_error && MAD.Status) {
8162 *offset += tvb_captured_length_remaining(tvb, *offset);
8163 return;
8164 }
8165 proto_tree_add_item(parentTree, hf_opa_vendor, tvb, *offset, -1, ENC_NA0x00000000);
8166
8167 col_append_str(pinfo->cinfo, COL_INFO, "Vendor: (Dissector Not Implemented)");
8168
8169 expert_add_info_format(pinfo, NULL((void*)0), &ei_opa_mad_no_attribute_dissector,
8170 "Attribute Dissector Not Implemented (0x%x)", MAD.AttributeID);
8171
8172 *offset += tvb_captured_length_remaining(tvb, *offset);
8173 return;
8174}
8175
8176/* Parse Application Specific Management Packets */
8177/* TBD: Replace with dissector table to call other possible dissectors */
8178static void parse_APPLICATION_MANAGEMENT(proto_tree *parentTree, packet_info *pinfo, tvbuff_t *tvb, gint *offset)
8179{
8180 MAD_t MAD;
8181
8182 if (!parse_MAD_Common(parentTree, pinfo, tvb, offset, &MAD)) {
8183 return;
8184 }
8185 if (!pref_parse_on_mad_status_error && MAD.Status) {
8186 *offset += tvb_captured_length_remaining(tvb, *offset);
8187 return;
8188 }
8189 proto_tree_add_item(parentTree, hf_opa_application, tvb, *offset, -1, ENC_NA0x00000000);
8190
8191 col_append_str(pinfo->cinfo, COL_INFO, "Application: (Dissector Not Implemented)");
8192
8193 expert_add_info_format(pinfo, NULL((void*)0), &ei_opa_mad_no_attribute_dissector,
8194 "Attribute Dissector Not Implemented (0x%x)", MAD.AttributeID);
8195
8196 *offset += tvb_captured_length_remaining(tvb, *offset);
8197 return;
8198}
8199
8200/* Parse Reserved Management Packets --- ERROR */
8201static void parse_RESERVED_MANAGEMENT(proto_tree *parentTree, packet_info *pinfo, tvbuff_t *tvb, gint *offset)
8202{
8203 MAD_t MAD;
8204
8205 if (!parse_MAD_Common(parentTree, pinfo, tvb, offset, &MAD)) {
8206 return;
8207 }
8208 if (!pref_parse_on_mad_status_error && MAD.Status) {
8209 *offset += tvb_captured_length_remaining(tvb, *offset);
8210 return;
8211 }
8212 proto_tree_add_item(parentTree, hf_opa_reservedmclass, tvb, *offset, -1, ENC_NA0x00000000);
8213
8214 col_append_str(pinfo->cinfo, COL_INFO, "Reserved: (Dissector Not Implemented)");
8215
8216 expert_add_info_format(pinfo, NULL((void*)0), &ei_opa_mad_no_attribute_dissector,
8217 "Attribute Dissector Not Implemented (0x%x)", MAD.AttributeID);
8218
8219 *offset += tvb_captured_length_remaining(tvb, *offset);
8220 return;
8221}
8222
8223/* Parse Unknown Management Packets --- WARNING */
8224/* TBD: Replace with dissector table to call other possible dissectors */
8225static void parse_UNKNOWN_MANAGEMENT(proto_tree *parentTree, packet_info *pinfo, tvbuff_t *tvb, gint *offset)
8226{
8227 MAD_t MAD;
8228
8229 if (!parse_MAD_Common(parentTree, pinfo, tvb, offset, &MAD)) {
8230 return;
8231 }
8232 if (!pref_parse_on_mad_status_error && MAD.Status) {
8233 *offset += tvb_captured_length_remaining(tvb, *offset);
8234 return;
8235 }
8236 proto_tree_add_item(parentTree, hf_opa_unknown, tvb, *offset, -1, ENC_NA0x00000000);
8237
8238 col_append_str(pinfo->cinfo, COL_INFO, "Unknown: (Dissector Not Implemented)");
8239
8240 expert_add_info_format(pinfo, NULL((void*)0), &ei_opa_mad_no_attribute_dissector,
8241 "Attribute Dissector Not Implemented (0x%x)", MAD.AttributeID);
8242
8243 *offset += tvb_captured_length_remaining(tvb, *offset);
8244 return;
8245}
8246
8247/* Main OPA MAD dissector */
8248static int dissect_opa_mad(tvbuff_t *tvb, packet_info *pinfo, proto_tree *tree, void *data _U___attribute__((unused)))
8249{
8250 gint offset = 0; /* Current Offset */
8251 guint8 management_class;
8252 guint16 etype, reserved;
8253 dissector_handle_t dissector_found = NULL((void*)0);
8254 gboolean parent_was_opa_fe = proto_is_frame_protocol(pinfo->layers, "opa.fe");
8255
8256 col_set_str(pinfo->cinfo, COL_PROTOCOL, "Omni-Path");
8257 col_clear_fence(pinfo->cinfo, COL_INFO);
8258
8259 /* management datagrams are determined by the source/destination QPs */
8260 if (pinfo->srcport == 0 || pinfo->srcport == 1 || pinfo->destport == 0
8261 || pinfo->destport == 1 || parent_was_opa_fe) {
8262 management_class = tvb_get_guint8(tvb, offset + 1);
8263 if (value_is_in_range(global_mad_vendor_class, management_class) ||
8264 value_is_in_range(global_mad_vendor_rmpp_class, management_class)) {
8265 /* parse vendor specific */
8266 parse_VENDOR_MANAGEMENT(tree, pinfo, tvb, &offset);
8267 } else if (value_is_in_range(global_mad_application_class, management_class)) {
8268 /* parse application specific */
8269 parse_APPLICATION_MANAGEMENT(tree, pinfo, tvb, &offset);
8270 } else if (value_is_in_range(global_mad_reserved_class, management_class)) {
8271 /* parse reserved classes */
8272 parse_RESERVED_MANAGEMENT(tree, pinfo, tvb, &offset);
8273 } else if (value_is_in_range(global_mad_opa_class, management_class)) {
8274 switch (management_class) {
8275 case SUBN_LID_ROUTED0x01: /* parse subn man lid routed */
8276 parse_SUBN_LID_ROUTED(tree, pinfo, tvb, &offset);
8277 break;
8278 case SUBN_DIRECTED_ROUTE0x81: /* parse subn directed route */
8279 parse_SUBN_DIRECTED_ROUTE(tree, pinfo, tvb, &offset);
8280 break;
8281 case SUBNADMN0x03: /* parse sub admin */
8282 parse_SUBNADMN(tree, pinfo, tvb, &offset);
8283 break;
8284 case PERFADMN0x32:
8285 parse_PERFADMN(tree, pinfo, tvb, &offset);
8286 break;
8287 case PERF0x04: /* parse performance */
8288 parse_PERF(tree, pinfo, tvb, &offset);
8289 break;
8290 default:
8291 parse_UNKNOWN_MANAGEMENT(tree, pinfo, tvb, &offset);
8292 break;
8293 }
8294 } else {
8295 /* parse Unknown classes */
8296 parse_UNKNOWN_MANAGEMENT(tree, pinfo, tvb, &offset);
8297 }
8298 } else { /* Normal Data Packet - Parse as such */
8299 etype = tvb_get_ntohs(tvb, offset);
8300 reserved = tvb_get_ntohs(tvb, offset + 2);
8301 dissector_found = dissector_get_uint_handle(ethertype_dissector_table, etype);
8302 if (dissector_found != NULL((void*)0) && (reserved == 0)) {
8303 proto_tree_add_item(tree, hf_opa_etype, tvb, offset, 2, ENC_BIG_ENDIAN0x00000000);
8304 offset += 2;
8305 proto_tree_add_item(tree, hf_opa_etype_reserved16, tvb, offset, 2, ENC_BIG_ENDIAN0x00000000);
8306 offset += 2;
8307
8308 call_dissector(dissector_found, tvb_new_subset_remaining(tvb, offset), pinfo, tree);
8309 }
8310 }
8311 return tvb_captured_length(tvb);
8312}

13556 proto_opa_mad = proto_register_protocol("Intel Omni-Path MAD", "OPA MAD", "opa.mad");
13557 opa_mad_handle = register_dissector("opa.mad", dissect_opa_mad, proto_opa_mad);
13558
13559 proto_register_field_array(proto_opa_mad, hf, array_length(hf)(sizeof hf / sizeof hf[0]));
13560 proto_register_subtree_array(ett, array_length(ett)(sizeof ett / sizeof ett[0]));
13561
13562 expert_opa_mad = expert_register_protocol(proto_opa_mad);
13563 expert_register_field_array(expert_opa_mad, ei, array_length(ei)(sizeof ei / sizeof ei[0]));
13564
13565 range_convert_str(&global_mad_vendor_class, OPA_VENDOR_RANGE_STR"0x09-0x0F", 0xFF);
13566 range_convert_str(&global_mad_vendor_rmpp_class, OPA_VENDOR_RMPP_RANGE_STR"0x30-0x31,0x33-0x4F", 0xFF);
13567 range_convert_str(&global_mad_application_class, OPA_APPLICATION_RANGE_STR"0x10-0x2F", 0xFF);
13568 range_convert_str(&global_mad_reserved_class, OPA_RESERVED_RANGE_STR"0x00,0x02,0x50-0x80,0x82-0xFF", 0xFF);
13569 range_convert_str(&global_mad_opa_class, OPA_MGMTCLASS_RANGE_STR"0x01,0x03-0x04,0x32,0x81", 0xFF);
13570
13571 opa_mad_module = prefs_register_protocol(proto_opa_mad, proto_reg_handoff_opa_mad);
13572 prefs_register_bool_preference(opa_mad_module, "parse_mad_error",
13573 "Enable Parsing of Mad Payload on Mad Status Error",
13574 "Attempt to parse mad payload even when MAD.Status is non-zero",
13575 &pref_parse_on_mad_status_error);
13576}

13578void proto_reg_handoff_opa_mad(void)
13579{
13580 eth_handle = find_dissector("eth");
13581 ethertype_dissector_table = find_dissector_table("ethertype");
13582}
